{
  "body": "During [today's discussion](http://colabti.org/irclogger/irclogger_log/perl6?date=2018-06-28#l910) remembering indirect method call syntax was brought up, which is writing\r\n\r\n```perl6\r\n$obj.meth: @args;\r\n```\r\n\r\nas\r\n\r\n```perl6\r\nmeth $obj: @args;\r\n```\r\n\r\nI went into the docs to see if this handy tip was listed already:\r\n\r\n```\r\nZoffix | moritz: the indirect invocant has the same syntax as method signature definition:\r\nZoffix | method foo(\\Invocant: \\arg1, \\arg2) { }\r\nZoffix | say foo Invocant: arg1, arg2;\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, I couldn't find where it's documented at all. I tried:\r\n* Searching for \"indirect\"; that didn't give any good results\r\n* Searched for \"indirect method call\" and then clicked \"try google\" link but google didn't find it either\r\n* Search for \":\" and skimmed the gazillion returned results, but I don't see anything relevant.",
